<DOC><DOCNO> AP880319-0016 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-03-19-88 0412EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-BRF--India-Avalanches     03-19 0125</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--India-Avalanches,0127</SECOND><HEAD>New Snow Slides Kill At Least 145 in Kashmir</HEAD><DATELINE>NEW DELHI, India (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   More avalanches crashed down on mountainvillages in the northern Kashmir state, killing at least 145 peopleand injuring more than 100, United News of India reported today.   The casualties in Friday's snow slides brought to at least 217the death toll from avalanches in the mountain state since snowstorms hit March 10.   UNI said the Friday's avalanches hit three villages in in Kargildistrict, about 90 miles northeast of the state's capital ofSrinagar.   The agency said senior government officials made aerial surveyof the affected areas and relief operations were under way. It saidroads to many of the affected villages were blocked by snow.</TEXT></DOC>